publication.abstract: The k-anonymity technique is widely used to provide location privacy protection for accessing location-based services (LBS), i.e., the exact location of a query initiator is cloaked into a spatial region that contains at least k indistinguishable users. publication.title: Efficient Evaluation of k-Range Nearest Neighbor Queries in Road Networks
publication.keyword: K Nearest Neighbor;Nearest Neighbor Queries;Query Answering;Query Processing;Road Network;Nearest Neighbor;
publication.abstract: A k-Range Nearest Neighbor (or kRNN for short) query in road networks finds the k nearest neighbors of every point on the road segments within a given query region based on the network distance.
